Ideensammlung erlymacs:

- integration mit dem maven erlang plugin:

-- open test for source, open source for test
-- inspects the pom to find the source directories
   --- knows standard directories via 
-- project source tree view

-- automatically starts erlang node for tests when a new maven project was opened.
   -- starts one erlang node per project it detects called erlymock-<project-name>
   -- runs mvn test -DtestNode=... -DshutdownTestNode=false

-- compile file keybinding(add compilation of single file in emacs, 
   to maven plugin add generation of compile command for source files)
   compiles the file directly on the test node, also used by maven

   -- memorizes wether maven already uploaded all modules or not

-- auto build on save

-- eunit test runner, that runs eunit directly in a specified node, 
   -- runs all tests or just single tests
   -- colors buffer according to test results

-- integrated coverage display


- write simple erlang tool for development support
--> simple access to shell


